text: Diane Loeffler (July 12, 1953 – November 16, 2019) was an American politician. She was a member of the Minnesota House of Representatives from 2005 through 2019. She was a member of the Minnesota Democratic–Farmer–Labor Party (DFL). Loeffler was also a health policy analyst and planner for Hennepin County. She was born in Minneapolis. Loeffler died in Minneapolis on November 16, 2019 of cancer, aged 66.State Rep.
